<p itemprop="description">A junior interaction designer creates user interfaces and interaction flows for digital services. They work under guidance to design user journeys, create wireframes and prototypes, while learning about user-centred design principles and accessibility requirements.</p>

<section class="role-details">
    <h2>Typical responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Design user interfaces and interaction flows for digital services</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Create wireframes, prototypes, and user journey maps</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Support user research activities and usability testing</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Learn and apply accessibility principles in interaction design</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Collaborate with content designers and developers on implementation</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Participate in design critiques and iteration cycles</li>
    </ul>
</section>

